    "scope": "World",
    "isDarkLogo": false,
    "originalRssUrl": "https://www.accessnow.org/feed/"
  },
  {
    "title": "Artificial Insecurity: access and availability in the age of AI",
    "link": "https://www.accessnow.org/artificial-insecurity-access-and-availability/?pk_campaign=feed&pk_kwd=artificial-insecurity-access-and-availability",
    "pubDate": "2026-02-19T07:57:31.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide has-light-gray-background-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<p><em>In the final part of our blog series on the dodgy</em> <em>digital security practices underlying advanced</em> <em>artificial intelligence (AI) tools</em>,<em> we explore how LLMs </em><strong><em>impact the availability of tools and systems. </em></strong><em>Catch up with parts </em><a href=\"https://www.accessnow.org/artificial-insecurity-compromising-confidentality/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em><strong>one</strong></em></a><em><strong> </strong>and </em><a href=\"https://www.accessnow.org/artificial-insecurity-information-integrity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em><strong>two</strong></em></a><em>.</em></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n</body></html>",
    "creator": "Daniel Leufer",
    "sourceTitle": "Access Now",
    "sheetCategory": "Human Rights + Democracy",
    "enforcedImage": null,
