  {
    "title": "From Sandvine to AppLogic Networks: a rebrand doesn’t mean reform",
    "link": "https://www.accessnow.org/press-release/from-sandvine-to-applogic-networks-a-rebrand-doesnt-mean-reform/",
    "pubDate": "2026-02-12T12:58:12.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><p><strong>Update: </strong>AppLogic responded to our letter on February 20, 2026. <strong><a href=\"https://www.accessnow.org/AppLogic-response-to-Access-Now\" type=\"link\" id=\"https://www.accessnow.org/AppLogic-response-to-Access-Now\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read their full response</a></strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\">\n\n\n\n<p>Access Now, alongside several human rights organizations and independent news platforms, are calling on AppLogic Networks (previously Sandvine) to substantiate its <a href=\"https://www.applogicnetworks.com/press-releases/commerce-removes-sandvine-from-entity-list-following-significant-corporate-reforms-to-protect-human-rights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>announced corporate reforms</strong></a></p></body></html>",
    "creator": "Amina Khan",
    "sourceTitle": "Access Now",
    "sheetCategory": "Human Rights + Democracy",
    "enforcedImage": null,
    "sourceDescription": "",
    "sourceLogo": "https://www.accessnow.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/cropped-favicon-32x32.png",
    "lang": "en",
    "scope": "World",
    "isDarkLogo": false,
    "originalRssUrl": "https://www.accessnow.org/feed/"
  },
  {
    "title": "Artificial Insecurity: threats to information integrity",
    "link": "https://www.accessnow.org/artificial-insecurity-information-integrity/?pk_campaign=feed&pk_kwd=artificial-insecurity-information-integrity",
    "pubDate": "2026-02-12T10:01:19.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide has-light-gray-background-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<p><em>In part two of our blog series on the dodgy</em> <em>digital security practices underlying advanced</em> <em>artificial intelligence (AI) tools</em>,<em> we explore how large-language models (LLMs) </em><strong><em>threaten information integrity</em></strong><em> and how to mitigate those threats</em><strong><em>. </em></strong><em>Catch up with </em><a href=\"https://www.accessnow.org/artificial-insecurity-compromising-confidentality/\"><em>part one here</em></a><em>.</em></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>Every week, <a href=\"https://openai.com/index/introducing-chatgpt-health/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">hundreds of millions of people</a> ask ChatGPT deep</p></body></html>",
